<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-05-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-05-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="646" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d646">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/711.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-05-05">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 5, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The President was legally elected, order prevails and the members of the
                            Cabinet seem to be favorably disposed towards American influence.
                            Instruction desired in regard to recognition.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Furniss</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>